able Transport Fund (SLGF) as an incentive to mainstream capital spending on sustainable travel through the SLGF, by requiring bidders to demonstrate how proposals contribute to a long term visio</span><span style="font-family:'Helvetica 55 Roman'; font-size:11pt">n for sustainable transport.</span></li><li style="font-family:Symbol; font-size:11pt; margin:6pt 0pt 6pt 28.06pt; padding-left:7.94pt; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Helvetica 55 Roman'; font-size:11pt">Require the Department for Transport (</span><span style="font-family:'Helvetica 55 Roman'; font-size:11pt">DfT</span><span style="font-family:'Helvetica 55 Roman'; font-size:11pt">) to review all </span><span style="font-family:'Helvetica 55 Roman'; font-size:11pt">post-2015 </span><span style="font-family:'Helvetica 55 Roman'; font-size:11pt">proposals for major schemes, and to work with scheme promoters to ensure that a full range of options have been considered</span><span style="font-family:'Helvetica 55 Roman'; font-size:11pt"> and that the proposals support their </span><span style="font-family:'Helvetica 55 Roman'; font-size:11pt">wider vision for sustainable transport.</span></li><li style="font-family:Symbol; font-size:11pt; margin:6pt 0pt 6pt 28.06pt; padding-left:7.94pt; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Helvetica 55 Roman'; font-size:11pt">Improve the support available for LEPs </span><span style="font-family:'Helvetica 55 Roman'; font-size:11pt">to understand</span><span style="font-family:'Helvetica 55 Roman'; font-size:11pt"> </span><span style="font-family:'Helvetica 55 Roman'; font-size:11pt">how sustainable transport can support their objectives and embed </span><span style="font-family:'Helvetica 55 Roman'; font-size:11pt">public transport, walking and cycling</span><span style="font-family:'Helvetica 55 Roman'; font-size:11pt"> in </span><span style="font-family:'Helvetica 55 Roman'; font-size:11pt">their priorities for investment, including through traini</span><s