inable transport should be </span><span style="font-family:'Helvetica 55 Roman'; font-size:11pt">regarded</span><span style="font-family:'Helvetica 55 Roman'; font-size:11pt"> as a key component of the strategic transport network. </span><span style="font-family:'Helvetica 55 Roman'; font-size:11pt">Most journeys are local, but high levels of car use for local trips is a major cause of congestion and poor journey time reliability. Journeys of un</span><span style="font-family:'Helvetica 55 Roman'; font-size:11pt">der five miles comprise o</span><span style="font-family:'Helvetica 55 Roman'; font-size:11pt">ver two thirds of all journeys. M</span><span style="font-family:'Helvetica 55 Roman'; font-size:11pt">ore than half of all such journeys are made by car, compared with around a third on foot, seven per cent by bus and just two per cent by bike. A quarter of car journeys </span><span style="font-family:'Helvetica 55 Roman'; font-size:11pt">are </span><span style="font-family:'Helvetica 55 Roman'; font-size:11pt">of less than two miles</span><span style="font-family:'Helvetica 55 Roman'; font-size:11pt">, </span><span style="font-family:'Helvetica 55 Roman'; font-size:11pt">contributing substantially to congestion and unreliability on existing networks.</span><span style="font-family:'Helvetica 55 Roman'; font-size:11pt"> </span><span style="font-family:'Helvetica 55 Roman'; font-size:11pt">Even many motorway journeys are single junction trips, especially in built-up areas.</span></li><li style="font-family:'Helvetica 55 Roman'; font-size:11pt; margin:6pt 0pt 6pt 14.88pt; padding-left:3.12pt; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Helvetica 55 Roman'; font-size:11pt">The potential benefit to </span><span style="font-family:'Helvetica 55 Roman'; font-size:11pt">local economies</span><span style="font-family:'Helvetica 55 Roman'; font-size:11pt"> </span><span style="font-family:'Helvetica 55 Roman'; font-size:11pt">from</span><span style="font-family:'Helvetica 55 Roman'; font-size:11pt"> </span><span style="font-family:'Helvetica 55 Roman'; font-size:11pt">refocusing local transport </span><span style="font-family:'Helvetica 55 Roman'; font-size:11pt">expenditure</span><span style="font-family:'Helvetica 55 Roman'; font-size:11pt"> </span><span style="font-family:'Helvetica 55 Roman'; font-size:11pt">on</span><span style="font-family:'Helvetica 55 Roman'; font-size:11pt"> tr</span><span style="font-family:'Helvetica 55 Roman'; font-size:11pt">ansforming local travel and </span><span style="font-family:'Helvetica 55 Roman'; font-size:11pt">reducing car use is huge</span><span style="font-family:'Helvetica 55 Roman'; font-size:11pt">, particularly in terms of reducing congestion and improving journey time reliability on existing networks.</span><span style="font-family:'Helvetica 55 Roman'; font-size:11pt"> Boosting use of sustainable transport, walking, cycling and public transport use would also deli</span><span style="font-family:'Helvetica 55 Roman'; font-size:11pt">ver a range of </span><span style="font-family:'Helvetica 55 Roman'; font-size:11pt">GVA and </span><span style="font-family:'Helvetica 55 Roman'; font-size:11pt">wider economic benefits including </span><span style="font-family:'Helvetica 55 Roman'; font-size:11pt">improved access to employment, greater workplace productivity, better quality of life, </span><span style="font-family:'Helvetica 55 Roman'; font-size:11pt">savings elsewhere in the economy (e.g. health costs of obesity and pollution), reducing social exclusion</span><span style="font-family:'Helvetica 55 Roman'; font-size:11pt"> </span><span style="font-family:'Helvetica 55 Roman'; font-size:11pt">and cre</span><span style="font-family:'Helvetica 55 Roman'; font-size:11pt">ating </span><span style="font-family:'Helvetica 55 Roman'; font-size:11pt">resilience</span><span style="font-family:'Helvetica 55 Roman'; font-size:11pt"> and competitive advantage in the development of a low carbon economy.</span></li><li style="font-family:'Helvetica 55 Roman'; font-size:11pt; margin:6pt 0pt 6pt 14.88pt; padding-left:3.12pt; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Helvetica 55 Roman'; font-size:11pt">In contrast, there</span><span style="font-family:'Helvetica 55 Roman'; font-size:11pt"> is strong evidence that prioritising investment in new road infrastructure offers poor value for money and does not deliver sustained economic benefit</span><span style="font-family:'Helvetica 55 Roman'; font-size:11pt">s. </span><span style="font-family:'Helvetica 55 Roman'; font-size:11pt">R</span><span style="font-family:'Helvetica 55 Roman'; font-size:11pt">oad schemes are often seen as a way to create jobs and growth</span><span style="font-family:'Helvetica 55 Roman'; font-size:11pt">, despite evidence that that there are more cost-effective solutions</span><span style="font-family:'Helvetica 55 Roman'; font-size:11pt">. </span><span style="font-family:'Helvetica 55 Roman'; font-size:11pt">Studies for </span><span style="font-family:'Helvetica 55 Roman'; font-size:11pt">DfT</span><span style="font-family:'Helvetica 55 Roman'; font-size:11pt"> </span><span style="font-family:'Helvetica 55 Roman'; font-size:11pt">have</span><span style="font-family:'Helvetica 55 Roman'; font-size:11pt"> concluded that the economic benefits of new roads are </span><span style="font-family:'Helvetica 55 Roman'; font-size:11pt">often small</span><span style="font-family:'Helvetica 55 Roman'; font-size:11pt"> </span><span style="font-family:'Helvetica 55 Roman'; font-size:11pt">and</span><span style="font-family:'Helvetica 55 Roman'; font-size:11pt"> short-lived </span><span style="font-family:'Helvetica 55 Roman'; font-size:11pt">and support a </span><span style="font-family:'Helvetica 55 Roman'; font-size:11pt">‘mod</span><span style="font-family:'Helvetica 55 Roman'; font-size:11pt">e agnostic’ approach, considering options for tackling congestion including public transport and demand restraint</span><span style="font-family:'Helvetica 55 Roman'; font-size:11pt"> ahead of new</span><span style="font-family:'Helvetica 55 Roman'; font-size:11pt"> roads.</span><span style="font-family:'Helvetica 55 Roman'; font-size:11pt"> I</span><span style="font-family:'Helvetica 55 Roman'; font-size:11pt">nvestment in new roads also risks diverting attention and resources from more effective </span><span style="font-family:'Helvetica 55 Roman'; font-size:11pt">and lower cost </span><span style="font-family:'Helvetica 55 Roman'; font-size:11pt">interventions</span><span style="font-family:'Helvetica 55 Roman'; font-size:11pt"> to p</span><span style="font-family:'Helvetica 55 Roman'; font-size:11pt">rovide alternatives to car use.</span></li><li style="font-family:'Helvetica 55 Roman'; font-size:11pt; margin:6pt 0pt 6pt 14.88pt; padding-left:3.12pt; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Helvetica 55 Roman'; font-size:11pt">Yet despite the evidence that i</span><span style="font-family:'Helvetica 55 Roman'; font-size:11pt">nvestment in public transport, walking, cycling and smarter choices programmes offers </span><span style="font-family:'Helvetica 55 Roman'; font-size:11pt">low cost, </span><span style="font-family:'Helvetica 55 Roman'; font-size:11pt">value for money and highly</span><span style="font-family:'Helvetica 55 Roman'; font-size:11pt"> effective ways to ta</span><span style="font-family:'Helvetica 55 Roman'; font-size:11pt">ckle transport problems and support the local econ</span><span style="font-family:'Helvetica 55 Roman'; font-size:11pt">omic agenda, this is not </span><span style="font-family:'Helvetica 55 Roman'; font-size:11pt">yet </span><span style="font-family:'Helvetica 55 Roman'; font-size:11pt">reflected in priorities for transport expenditure being developed by LTBs and </span><span style="font-family:'Helvetica 55 Roman'; font-size:11pt">LEPs</span><span style="font-family:'Helvetica 55 Roman'; font-size:11pt">. </span><span style="font-family:'Helvetica 55 Roman'; font-size:11pt">Sustrans</span><span style="font-family:'Helvetica 55 Roman'; font-size:11pt"> urges the committee to enquire into this issue further, and to make recommendations to ensure that </span><span style="font-family:'Helvetica 55 Roman'; font-size:11pt">local decision making on transport </span><span style="font-family:'Helvetica 55 Roman'; font-size:11pt">expenditure reflects the evidence and best practice on how best to tackle local transport issues, notably by refocusing investment on local sustainable travel and alternatives to car use.</span></li></ol><p style="margin:8.25pt 0pt"><span style="font-family:'Helvetica 55 Roman'; font-size:11pt; font-weight:bold">Single Local Growth Fund</span></p><ol start="10" type="1" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><li style="font-family:'Helvetica 55 Roman'; font-size:11pt; margin:8.25pt 0pt 8.25pt 17.85pt; orphans:0; text-indent:0pt; widows:0"><span style="font-family:'Helvetica 55 Roman'; font-size:11pt">We are concerned that </span><span style="font-family:'Helvetica 55 Roman'; font-size:11pt">the introduction of the </span><span style="font-family:'Helvetica 55 Roman'; font-size:11pt">SLGF</span><span style="font-family:'Helvetica 55 Roman'; font-size:11pt"> </span><span style="font-family:'Helvetica 55 Roman'; font-size:11pt">(including</span><span style="font-family:'Helvetica 55 Roman'; font-size:11pt"> </span><span style="font-family:'Helvetica 55 Roman'; font-size:11pt">all </span><span style="font-family:'Helvetica 55 Roman'; font-size:11pt">t</span><span style="font-family:'Helvetica 55 Roman'; font-size:11pt">ransport capital) </span><span style="font-family:'Helvetica 55 Roman'; font-size:11pt">means that growth is being prioritised above other public policy objectives, </span><span style="font-family:'Helvetica 55 Roman'; font-size:11pt">including</span><span style="font-family:'Helvetica 55 Roman'; font-size:11pt"> other statutory responsibilities such as road safety</spa